Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves computational geometry, as it deals with subsets of a given set, which can be represented as points in a geometric space. Hence, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory, as it deals with problems such as $k$-Internal Out-Branching and Long Directed Cycle. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Graph Theory) are also possible sub-categories.
